This game is well designed and the development of the game has been very successful. One of my three year old sons favorite games.

This game will keep your child entertained for hours!  There  are so many options and combinations in each of the four play sets that your childs imagination just blossoms!  My autistic 5yr old is in love with this appt

Why she loves it I don't know as there doesn't appear to be much to do. That's not my problem with it though my gripe with it when she leaves it and the screen turns of the app still runs. I the sound still plays and this drains the battery. Fix this and u get 5 stars.

I was in a rush looking for app for my 3yo babies and after reading a couple of reviews here I decided to buy it. I was bias towards it because I had the free version before and both of my babies loved it.  There are not instructions of how to play the game. My children gave it a try and didn't like it at all, it's not intuitive enough, even for me... or maybe our expectations were higher. I still don't understand how come there are so many good reviews of it. My conclusion is that I must be missing somethi

My 2 year old loves it. I thought it would be too complex but she found it very natural and engaging. App is well designed, great to look at, and individual elements in each scene work well (particularly switching from day to night on scene 3!).
Keeps our three year old daughter out of trouble when she's tired!

My students love it. Great reinforcement activity
I love how interactive this app is.  Great for a curious toddler.  I've never seen an app like this before.

This may not seem like a big deal but it was for us. We were at a wifi hotspot and so decided to download this game for my child. Then, after it was finished downloading, we went home only to find out the game could not be played unless we downloaded additional software.   Customers should be informed that an app requires the downloading of other apps to function properly.
Awesome and fun

Both my 1.5 and 5 year old love this app. I have it on my phone and tablet and it's a real life saver. It's like having 4 whole sets of toys with you all the time in your back pocket.   The only thing is that they sometimes fight over it because they love it so much.  For a tired parent who needs a rest from running after a toddler it's perfect.  It's brilliant and I would buy more like this, especially train sets. Keep up the good work.

My almost three year old loves this app. There's enough variety in all the playgrounds to hold his interest. His favourite is the day/night one. I've held back a star because I would like to see even more interactivity in each playground. What's there is great but IMO there's lots more that could be added. Overall it's a great concept (and no ads!).
